#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.20:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Sāraṇīyavagga"
msgstr "2. Warm-hearted"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Dutiyamaraṇassatisutta"
msgstr "20. Mindfulness of Death (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nātike viharati giñjakāvasathe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Nādika in the brick house."

msgctxt "an6.20:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.20:1.3"
msgid ""
"“maraṇassati, bhikkhave, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā "
"amatogadhā amatapariyosānā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when mindfulness of death is developed and cultivated it’s very "
"fruitful and beneficial. It culminates in the deathless and ends with the "
"deathless."

msgctxt "an6.20:1.4"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, maraṇassati kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti "
"mahānisaṃsā amatogadhā amatapariyosānā?"
msgstr ""
"And how is mindfulness of death developed and cultivated to be very fruitful "
"and beneficial, to culminate in the deathless and end with the deathless?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.307"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: patihitāya → paṭihitāya (s1-3, pts1) | paṭigatāya (mr)
msgctxt "an6.20:2.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu divase nikkhante rattiyā patihitāya iti "
"paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "As day passes by and night draws close, a mendicant reflects:"

msgctxt "an6.20:2.2"
msgid "‘bahukā kho me paccayā maraṇassa—"
msgstr "‘I might die of many causes."

msgctxt "an6.20:2.3"
msgid ""
"ahi vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya, vicchiko vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya, satapadī vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya;"
msgstr "A snake might bite me, or a scorpion or centipede might sting me."

msgctxt "an6.20:2.4"
msgid "tena me assa kālakiriyā, so mamassa antarāyo."
msgstr "And if I died from that it would be an obstacle to me."

msgctxt "an6.20:2.5"
msgid ""
"Upakkhalitvā vā papateyyaṃ, bhattaṃ vā me bhuttaṃ byāpajjeyya, pittaṃ vā me "
"kuppeyya, semhaṃ vā me kuppeyya, satthakā vā me vātā kuppeyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Or I might stumble off a cliff, or get food poisoning, or suffer a "
"disturbance of bile, phlegm, or piercing winds."

msgctxt "an6.20:2.6"
msgid "tena me assa kālakiriyā, so mamassa antarāyo’ti."
msgstr "And if I died from that it would be an obstacle to me.’"

msgctxt "an6.20:2.7"
msgid "Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "That mendicant should reflect:"

msgctxt "an6.20:2.8"
msgid ""
"‘atthi nu kho me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīnā, ye me assu rattiṃ kālaṃ "
"karontassa antarāyāyā’ti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"‘Are there any bad, unskillful qualities that I haven’t given up, which "
"might be an obstacle to me if I die tonight?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:3.1"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:"
msgstr "Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that"

msgctxt "an6.20:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘atthi me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīnā, ye me assu rattiṃ kālaṃ karontassa "
"antarāyāyā’ti, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ pahānāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca "
"appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"there are such bad, unskillful qualities. Then in order to give them up they "
"should apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, "
"mindfulness, and situational awareness."

msgctxt "an6.20:3.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ādittacelo vā ādittasīso vā tasseva celassa vā "
"sīsassa vā nibbāpanāya adhimattaṃ chandañca vāyāmañca ussāhañca ussoḷhiñca "
"appaṭivāniñca satiñca sampajaññañca kareyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose your clothes or head were on fire. In order to extinguish it, you’d "
"apply intense enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, "
"and situational awareness."

msgctxt "an6.20:3.4"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tena bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ pahānāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca "
"appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ. (2)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, in order to give up those bad, unskillful qualities, that "
"mendicant should apply outstanding enthusiasm …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:4.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:"
msgstr "But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that"

msgctxt "an6.20:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīnā, ye me assu rattiṃ kālaṃ "
"karontassa antarāyāyā’ti, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena "
"vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (3)"
msgstr ""
"there are no such bad, unskillful qualities. Then that mendicant should "
"meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.308"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:5.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rattiyā nikkhantāya divase patihite iti "
"paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Or else, as night passes by and day draws close, a mendicant reflects:"

msgctxt "an6.20:5.2"
msgid "‘bahukā kho me paccayā maraṇassa—"
msgstr "‘I might die of many causes."

msgctxt "an6.20:5.3"
msgid ""
"ahi vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya, vicchiko vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya, satapadī vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya;"
msgstr "A snake might bite me, or a scorpion or centipede might sting me."

msgctxt "an6.20:5.4"
msgid "tena me assa kālakiriyā so mamassa antarāyo."
msgstr "And if I died from that it would be an obstacle to me."

msgctxt "an6.20:5.5"
msgid ""
"Upakkhalitvā vā papateyyaṃ, bhattaṃ vā me bhuttaṃ byāpajjeyya, pittaṃ vā me "
"kuppeyya, semhaṃ vā me kuppeyya, satthakā vā me vātā kuppeyyuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Or I might stumble off a cliff, or get food poisoning, or suffer a "
"disturbance of bile, phlegm, or piercing winds."

msgctxt "an6.20:5.6"
msgid "tena me assa kālakiriyā so mamassa antarāyo’ti."
msgstr "And if I died from that it would be an obstacle to me.’"

msgctxt "an6.20:5.7"
msgid "Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "That mendicant should reflect:"

msgctxt "an6.20:5.8"
msgid ""
"‘atthi nu kho me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīnā, ye me assu divā kālaṃ "
"karontassa antarāyāyā’ti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"‘Are there any bad, unskillful qualities that I haven’t given up, which "
"might be an obstacle to me if I die today?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:6.1"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:"
msgstr "Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that"

msgctxt "an6.20:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘atthi me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīnā, ye me assu divā kālaṃ karontassa "
"antarāyāyā’ti, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ pahānāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca "
"appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"there are such bad, unskillful qualities. Then in order to give them up they "
"should apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, "
"mindfulness, and situational awareness."

msgctxt "an6.20:6.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ādittacelo vā ādittasīso vā tasseva celassa vā "
"sīsassa vā nibbāpanāya adhimattaṃ chandañca vāyāmañca ussāhañca ussoḷhiñca "
"appaṭivāniñca satiñca sampajaññañca kareyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose your clothes or head were on fire. In order to extinguish it, you’d "
"apply intense enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, "
"and situational awareness."

msgctxt "an6.20:6.4"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tena bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ pahānāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca "
"appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ. (5)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, in order to give up those bad, unskillful qualities, that "
"mendicant should apply outstanding enthusiasm …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:7.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:"
msgstr "But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that"

msgctxt "an6.20:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīnā, ye me assu divā kālaṃ karontassa "
"antarāyāyā’ti, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ "
"ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. (6)"
msgstr ""
"there are no such bad, unskillful qualities. Then that mendicant should "
"meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:8.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, maraṇassati evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti "
"mahānisaṃsā amatogadhā amatapariyosānā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Mindfulness of death, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very "
"fruitful and beneficial. It culminates in the deathless and ends with the "
"deathless.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.20:8.2"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.20:8.3"
msgid "Sāraṇīyavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.20:9.1"
msgid "Dve sāraṇī nisāraṇīyaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.20:9.2"
msgid "bhaddakaṃ anutappiyaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.20:9.3"
msgid "Nakulaṃ soppamacchā ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.20:9.4"
msgid "dve honti maraṇassatīti."
msgstr ""
